security_findings.evidence:
Unpatched decompilation (ndis_unpatched.c, ndisFreePerProcessorSlot @ 0x140050390):
```
  v5 = ndisMaxNumberOfProcessors;
  for ( i = 0; i < v5; *(_QWORD *)((v7 << 12) + BugCheckParameter2) = 0 )
    v7 = i++;
```

Patched decompilation (ndis_patched.c, ndisFreePerProcessorSlot @ 0x140054E30):
```
  for ( i = 0; i < ndisMaxNumberOfProcessors; *(_QWORD *)((v6 << 12) + BugCheckParameter2) = 0 )
    v6 = i++;
```
Both bound by ndisMaxNumberOfProcessors and store one 8-byte zero per stride. The tag check ndisBugCheckEx(0x2C, ...) is identical in both.
